<h2> HOLLY JOLLY CHRISMAS </h2>

<h2 id="capo-on-1st-fret">Capo on 1st fretâ€¦</h2>

<p>If you want to play along with the album version, toss a capo on the first fret! Note, in my video lesson Iâ€™m not using a capo.</p>

<h2 id="chords">Chords</h2>

<p>Note the optional pinky additions, on the high E-string:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>---0+3---2+3---0+3---
---1-----3-----0-----
---0-----2-----0-----
---2-----0-----2-----
---3-----------2-----
---------------0-----
   C     D     Em
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="simple-chorus-riff-high-e-string">Simple chorus riff (high E string)</h2>

